eip712Domain().details: returns the fields and values that describe the domain separator used by this contract for EIP-712 signature.

getDomainManagerRole(bytes32).details: Creates a unique role identifier for each domain manager

returns._0: bytes32 The role identifier for domain managers

getDomainOwnerRole(bytes32).details: Creates a unique role identifier for each domain owner

returns._0: bytes32 The role identifier for domain owners

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

getRoleMembers(bytes32).details: Return all accounts that have `role` WARNING: This operation will copy the entire storage to memory, which can be quite expensive. This is designed to mostly be used by view accessors that are queried without any gas fees. Developers should keep in mind that this function has an unbounded cost, and using it as part of a state-changing function may render the function uncallable if the set grows to a point where copying to memory consumes too much gas to fit in a block.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(address,address,address).details: Initializes inherited contracts, grants roles and configures external contracts

params._controller: Address of the domain controller contract
params._resolver: Address of the DNS resolver contract
params._rootKMSKey: Address with ROOT_KMS_KEY_ROLE for verifying KMS proofs

isDomainEncumbered(bytes32).details: A domain is encumbered if the domain is owned by this contract and has no owner or manager roles

returns._0: bool True if the domain is encumbered, false otherwise

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: This function is called when the contract is the recipient of an ERC721 token

params.data: Additional data with no specified format, not used
params.from: The address that transferred the token
params.operator: The address that initiated the transfer
params.tokenId: The identifier of the token being transferred

returns._0: bytes4 The function selector for ERC721Receiver

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

removeKMSKey(bytes32).details: Only the domain owner can remove the KMS key

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

retrieveDomain(bytes32,address).details: Only the domain owner can retrieve the domain, and no other owner or manager roles should exist at that point

params.to: The address to transfer the domain to

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setDNSRecords(bytes32,bytes,bytes).details: Can only be called by accounts with the domain manager role or anyone in case of no manager

params.records: The DNS record data to set
params.sig: Cryptographic signature proving the record update is authorized

setKMSContract(bytes32,address).details: Only the domain owner can set the KMS contract

params.kmsContract: The address of the KMS contract

setKMSKey(bytes32,address,bytes).details: KMS key is set only if the proof from root KMS server is valid for the KMS contract for the domain

params.kmsSigner: The address of the KMS signer
params.proof: The proof to verify the KMS key

setWhoIsDelegatee(bytes32,address).details: Only domain owner can set it

params.delegatee: The address that can set the WHOIS records

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Overrides ERC165, AccessControl, and AccessControlEnumerable implementations

returns._0: bool True if the interface is supported

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

DNSResolver().notice: Contract that manages DNS records for domains

ROOT_KMS_KEY_ROLE().notice: Role used for verifying KMS proofs when setting domain KMS keys

SET_RECORDS_TYPEHASH().notice: EIP-712 domain separator for setting DNS records

domainController().notice: Contract that manages domain ownership as NFTs

getDomainManagerRole(bytes32).notice: Gets the role identifier for domain managers

getDomainOwnerRole(bytes32).notice: Gets the role identifier for domain owners

isDomainEncumbered(bytes32).notice: Checks if a domain is encumbered

kmsContracts(bytes32).notice: Maps domain IDs to their KMS contract addresses

kmsKeys(bytes32).notice: Maps domain IDs to their KMS signer addresses

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Handles the receipt of a single ERC721 token

removeKMSKey(bytes32).notice: Removes the KMS key for a domain

retrieveDomain(bytes32,address).notice: Transfers the domain from the contract to the specified address

setDNSRecords(bytes32,bytes,bytes).notice: Sets DNS records for a domain after verifying signature from enclave KMS key

setKMSContract(bytes32,address).notice: Sets the KMS contract for a domain

setKMSKey(bytes32,address,bytes).notice: Sets the KMS key for a domain after verifying the proof

setWhoIsDelegatee(bytes32,address).notice: Sets IAM permission for the delegatee to manage WHOIS records on the DNS provider

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if the contract supports an interface
